author: Nerdstalgic
description:
When it comes to heist films, few do it better than Ocean’s Eleven. With a star-studded cast led by George Clooney and Brad Pitt, razor-sharp direction from Steven Soderbergh, and a pitch-perfect tone, Ocean’s Eleven didn’t just succeed—it redefined the modern heist genre.

But what makes this 2001 remake of the original Frank Sinatra Rat Pack film so enduring? Why does it still hold up over two decades later—even after a wave of sequels and a soft reboot?

#oceanseleven #georgeclooney #bradpitt #nerdstalgic
title: When A Remake Is WAY Better Than The Original...
